(You): How much does a T1 cost these days?

(Steven): It depends on your distance from the CLEC, but you're looking at $600/mo or thereabouts.

(You): thanks. That's still really high. I thought it came way down since SDSL does almost as well for a lot less!

(Steven): Yeah, with MPLS leases and cable modems being what they are T1s aren't very useful anymore.

(You): which is why you'd think prices would get lower to compete... but I guess the technology is just going obsolete.

(Steven): Exactly - way too expensive to maintain copper that way.

(You): one day it'll be all fiber!

(Steven): Sayin'.

